Things to Know Before Buying This Bag:💼 

• Wide Shoulder Strap: Super comfy for long commutes or travel days! 
• Hidden Inner Pocket: Perfect for stashing your small essentials like keys, lip balm, or headphones.
• Zippered Section: There’s a secure pocket inside where I usually keep my iPad or notebook. 
• Button Closure: The main compartment only has a button closure, so if you’re using public transport, just be a little extra careful.
• Spacious Interior: I carry my work essentials, lunch, and even my crochet projects🫶🏻 everything fits easily! You can check the size in the video for a better idea.

🌻So here’s what I wish I knew sooner—and what I want you to remember:

💌 Start slow. Your first project doesn’t need to be perfect; it just needs to be yours.

💌Count your stitches, but don’t count yourself out.

💌Frogging isn’t failure—it’s choosing to do it better.

💌Your tension will even out—so will your self-doubt.

💌Practice doesn’t make perfect, but it does make progress.

So save this for the days you want to quit, the days your project looks wonky, or your hook feels heavy. Because trust me—you’re learning with every loop.💌🤍
